qas.question: What pub is feature on the British soap opera Coronation Street?
What pub is featured on EastEnders?
What channel is EastEnders broadcast on?
What channel is home to the soap opera Emmerdale?
What pub is featured on Emmerdale?

context: The major soap operas on British television each feature a pub, and these pubs have become household names. <a0_0>The Rovers Return<a0_0/> is the pub in Coronation Street, the British soap broadcast on <a3_0>ITV<a3_0/>. <a1_0>The Queen Vic<a1_0/> (short for the Queen Victoria) is the pub in EastEnders, the major soap on <a2_0>BBC One<a2_0/> and <a4_0>the Woolpack<a4_0/> in ITV's Emmerdale. The sets of each of the three major television soap operas have been visited by some of the members of the royal family, including Queen Elizabeth II. The centrepiece of each visit was a trip into the Rovers, the Queen Vic, or the Woolpack to be offered a drink. The Bull in the BBC Radio 4 soap opera The Archers is an important meeting point.
